<paragraph blockId="11.[136,775,2032,2089]" lastBlockId="11.[835,1475,189,437]" pageId="11" pageNumber="577">
Colour photographs of a live specimen published by 
<bibRefCitation author="Turak E &amp; DeVantier L" pageId="11" pageNumber="577" refId="ref11021" refString="Turak E &amp; DeVantier L (2011) Field guide to the reef-building corals of Brunei Darussalam. Fisheries Department, Ministry of Industry and Primary Resources, Government of Brunei Darussalam, 256 pp." type="book" year="2011">Turak &amp; DeVantier (2011)</bibRefCitation>
were taken in 
<collectingCountry box="[511,618,2064,2088]" name="Indonesia" pageId="11" pageNumber="577">Indonesia</collectingCountry>
. An additional black and white photograph (locality not indicated) only shows a quarter portion of the upper surface of a thin, coral, which could be a juvenile specimen of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Claereboudt &amp; Hoeksema" authorityYear="1987" box="[1332,1443,253,277]" class="Anthozoa" family="Fungiidae" genus="Fungia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scleractinia" pageId="11" pageNumber="577" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="species" species="spinifer">
<emphasis box="[1332,1443,253,277]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="577">L. spinifer</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
or belong to 
<emphasis box="[948,1154,285,309]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="577">
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Alcock" baseAuthorityYear="1893" box="[948,1151,285,309]" class="Anthozoa" family="Fungiidae" genus="Cycloseris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scleractinia" pageId="11" pageNumber="577" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="species" species="fragilis">Cycloseris fragilis</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
Specimens of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Claereboudt &amp; Hoeksema" authorityYear="1987" box="[1320,1432,285,309]" class="Anthozoa" family="Fungiidae" genus="Fungia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scleractinia" pageId="11" pageNumber="577" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="species" species="spinifer">
<emphasis box="[1320,1432,285,309]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="577">L. spinifer</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are shaped like a saucer, usually with a thick, bulging central area, a corallum margin turning upward, and strongly developed lower order costae (
<bibRefCitation author="Claereboudt M &amp; Hoeksema BW" pageId="11" pageNumber="577" pagination="303 - 309" refId="ref8327" refString="Claereboudt M &amp; Hoeksema BW (1987) Fungia (Verrillofungia) spinifer spec. nov., a new scleractinian coral (Fungiidae) from the Indo-Malayan region. Zoologische Mededelingen Leiden, 61: 303 - 309." type="journal article" year="1987">Claereboudt &amp; Hoeksema, 1987</bibRefCitation>
; Hoeksema, 1989, 1993).
</paragraph>
